  <div class="space-y-6 my-8">
    <div class="border-b border-neutral-200 pb-4">
      <h3 class="font-semibold text-neutral-900 mb-2">Can I use SafetyWing for US healthcare?</h3>
      <p class="text-neutral-600">
        SafetyWing limits US coverage to 15 days per 90-day period and has no provider network. You'd pay full self-pay rates (often 2-3x negotiated rates) and claim for reimbursement. It's designed for travel emergencies, not ongoing US care. GeoBlue's BCBS network provides far better US access.
      </p>
    </div>

    <div class="border-b border-neutral-200 pb-4">
      <h3 class="font-semibold text-neutral-900 mb-2">What if I develop a health condition while on SafetyWing?</h3>
      <p class="text-neutral-600">
        Initial emergency treatment may be covered. But ongoing management of that condition wouldn't be—it would become a "pre-existing condition." This is where emergency-only coverage shows its limits. With GeoBlue, conditions that develop while covered remain covered.
      </p>
    </div>

    <div class="border-b border-neutral-200 pb-4">
      <h3 class="font-semibold text-neutral-900 mb-2">Is GeoBlue only for US citizens?</h3>
      <p class="text-neutral-600">
        GeoBlue primarily serves US citizens and permanent residents. Some plans may accept non-Americans with strong US ties. If you're not American, verify eligibility before applying—and consider whether BCBS network access (GeoBlue's key advantage) is relevant to you.
      </p>
    </div>

    <div class="border-b border-neutral-200 pb-4">
      <h3 class="font-semibold text-neutral-900 mb-2">Why is SafetyWing so much cheaper?</h3>
      <p class="text-neutral-600">
        SafetyWing covers much less. They only pay for emergencies—rare events for most healthy young travelers. GeoBlue covers everything including routine care, specialist visits, prescriptions, and mental health. You're comparing emergency-only coverage to comprehensive health insurance.
      </p>
    </div>

    <div class="border-b border-neutral-200 pb-4">
      <h3 class="font-semibold text-neutral-900 mb-2">Can I switch from SafetyWing to GeoBlue later?</h3>
      <p class="text-neutral-600">
        Yes, but any conditions you develop while on SafetyWing become pre-existing for GeoBlue's underwriting. They may exclude those conditions or apply loading. It's generally better to start with appropriate coverage than to upgrade later when health issues have emerged.
      </p>
    </div>

    <div class="border-b border-neutral-200 pb-4">
      <h3 class="font-semibold text-neutral-900 mb-2">Does GeoBlue cover mental health?</h3>
      <p class="text-neutral-600">
        Yes, though coverage levels vary by plan. GeoBlue offers moderate mental health coverage including therapy and psychiatry with some limits. It's not as comprehensive as BUPA Global's mental health parity, but it's far better than SafetyWing's zero coverage.
      </p>
